                    "exact": "Allan",
                    "prefix": " Although slightly tongue-in-cheek in its portrayal of Salomania as evidence of British morals corrupted by American dance—or Englishness by Americanness—and in its suggestion that danger to public morals in England lies partly in the exclusion of men from the dance, the Salome Dinner Dance article makes an important point when it implies that the effect of",
